<br>
Anyway how about three additional songs.<br>
<br>
Song of spears - Slight boost to piercing damage dealt by the group + increase to piercing resist.<br>
<br>
Song of Swords - Slight boost to slashing damage dealt by the group + increase to slash resist.<br>
<br>
Song of Hammers - Slight boost to crushing dmg dealt by the group + increase to crush resist.<br>
<br>
These would stack with the normal dmg chant and be about 50%* as effective (but comming at later levels, so last one would be at level 50). The resist portion wouldn't be massive but enough to make the chants worthwhile. Mostly they'd be used only when grouping multiple skalds, but they could also be used effectively instead of the normal damage chant when it would be tactically advantagious. These are very tactical songs, not useful in all situations but a hell of a lot less fiddly then the single resist songs. They also fit happily into Midgards supposed theme of &quot;the melee realm&quot; and should help the thinking skald from falling too far behind tanks and recognised hybrid tanks.<br>
<br>
*The dmg and resist needs to be worked out so that it would be an advantage to use these when using a dmg type and fighting against the same dmg type, while not creating excessive dmg when grouped with someone doing the normal chant. That said perhaps the dmg amount needs to be about 80% of the standard add with a reasonable enough resist element reducing their damage to a point where the skald will be doing better then if he'd just stuck with the full damage of the standard dmg buff. Then the damage bonus could be reduced to half of the standard dmg adds level when stacked on top of the standard dmg add. <br>
<br>
It would be interesting to see Skalds forming damage type groups. Although Skalds can't have peircing weapons, but they could group with hunters and savages and collectively hunt down those peskier Spero's. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showPrevMessage?topicID=43.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showNextMessage?topicID=43.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=43.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.emailToFriend?topicID=43.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.threadControl?topicID=43.topic><img src=http://www.stuckathome.com/skalded/images/closethread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=43.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=43.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action